# last_index_of via reverse scan.
*last_index_of(xs as Vec of i64, t as i64) returns i64
    i is xs.length - 1
    while i >= 0
        if xs.get(i) equals t
            return i
        i is i - 1
    -1

*main
    xs is vec()
    xs.push(1)
    xs.push(2)
    xs.push(2)
    xs.push(3)
    xs.push(2)
    log last_index_of(xs, 2)
    log last_index_of(xs, 9)
